From Bill Mayhew Subject Re mysterious TV problem source If the set is direct line powered try checking the likely to be there hybrid regulator module down stream from the volt Several sets I've looked at use a volt The regulators have a tendency to short out making the safety circuits shut down the EHT supply Try putting the set on a Variac or adjustable transformer and lower the AC input voltage to the set to about If the set operates nromally then you know you've got a shorted There are myriad other areas for problems but I've seen the one above several Also if the set uses one the trippler module may be shot that's fairly Bill Mayhew NEOUCOM Computer Services Department Rootstown OH USA phone